==Latin==
==={{initialism}}===
{{wikipediapar|Ab urbe condita}}
'''AUC'''
# Ab Urbe Condita, meaning "from the founding of the city" (the city being [[w:Rome|Rome]]), for counting [[year]]s for a [[date]].  The founding is taken to have been 753 BC.
# Anno Urbis Conditae, meaning "in the year from the founding of the city" (the city again being [[w:Rome|Rome]]).
